WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:40.081 --> 00:00:42.792
Man. thought you'd be
off the clock by five.

3
00:00:42.802 --> 00:00:45.680
They keep you on call?
Shit luck.

4
00:00:46.337 --> 00:00:48.089
Cap said I could leave
my gun and badge

5
00:00:48.092 --> 00:00:50.010
if I went home to listen to my old lady

6
00:00:50.013 --> 00:00:54.817
go on and on about her online shopping
or whatever the hell she did all day.

7
00:00:55.020 --> 00:00:58.037
That’s what you get for choosing
the life of a public servant.

8
00:00:58.099 --> 00:01:00.071
It just had to fucking rain.

9
00:01:00.560 --> 00:01:03.146
Hm? What the hell you doin'?
Back it up.

10
00:01:03.229 --> 00:01:04.411
Looking to get shot?

11
00:01:31.844 --> 00:01:33.417
Got us a cyber psycho!

12
00:01:33.651 --> 00:01:35.486
Raise MaxTac now!

13
00:02:31.067 --> 00:02:32.735
We need to fry the system fast.

14
00:02:32.939 --> 00:02:34.947
Freak's supporting military-grade ICE!

15
00:02:35.024 --> 00:02:37.711
Meaning that our tech isn't?
Get to it!

16
00:03:20.943 --> 00:03:22.496
So. what do you think?

17
00:03:22.952 --> 00:03:25.330
Still warm. that.
Couple hours old.

18
00:03:25.413 --> 00:03:27.540
Lifted from the edgerunner
who scrolled it.

19
00:03:27.557 --> 00:03:29.225
Straight off the street.

20
00:03:29.342 --> 00:03:30.760
So. what!

21
00:03:30.877 --> 00:03:34.172
Doc. hey. you gotta tell me
who keeps feeding you these nuggets.

22
00:03:34.222 --> 00:03:35.599
Kurosaki. Who else?

23
00:03:35.661 --> 00:03:38.747
Ain't no other editor who churns out
BDs that sweet and preem.

24
00:03:38.885 --> 00:03:41.033
Won't pull nothin' like that
off the shelf. neither.

25
00:03:41.134 --> 00:03:44.273
No shit. Brain's still buzzing.
Gonna be sick.

26
00:03:44.310 --> 00:03:46.312
Slow. deep breaths. choom.

27
00:03:46.436 --> 00:03:49.105
Just left the head of a
skezzed-out chrome junkie.

28
00:03:49.229 --> 00:03:51.147
Cyberpsychosis ain't no joke.

29
00:03:51.231 --> 00:03:54.359
Anyway. either hurt or don't.
got more chips for you to slot.

30
00:03:54.415 --> 00:03:55.791
Really? What?

31
00:03:55.828 --> 00:03:57.997
Something special.

32
00:03:59.255 --> 00:04:01.757
Huh? Cut the shit. man!

33
00:04:13.205 --> 00:04:14.205
Huh?

34
00:04:15.669 --> 00:04:18.447
Cycle suspended
due to insufficient funds.

35
00:04:18.450 --> 00:04:21.368
- Geez. not again.
- Cycle suspended due to in...

36
00:04:21.594 --> 00:04:25.187
It was a tragic scene in Westbrook
today when a corporate convoy

37
00:04:25.190 --> 00:04:27.660
- was ambushed by 6th Street…
- God. Mom.

38
00:04:30.311 --> 00:04:31.311
Morning. Miho.

39
00:04:31.314 --> 00:04:33.066
If you keep sleeping on the couch.

40
00:04:33.171 --> 00:04:35.066
gonna get early onset arthritis.

41
00:04:35.069 --> 00:04:37.887
I know. Just dead
after my night shift. is all.

42
00:04:38.025 --> 00:04:41.274
You and the washing machine both.
Forget to re-up it?

43
00:04:41.740 --> 00:04:42.907
Yeah.

44
00:04:42.910 --> 00:04:44.786
I'll take care of it later. okay?

45
00:04:44.898 --> 00:04:48.231
Oh. money. right.
You mentioned a reef update for class.

46
00:04:48.246 --> 00:04:50.123
That happen yet?
When'd you say you need it?

47
00:04:50.126 --> 00:04:53.917
No. no. It's fine.
Got Doc to handle it.

48
00:04:54.877 --> 00:04:58.172
- What do you mean "handle it"?
- I'm good. All set.

49
00:04:58.337 --> 00:05:00.237
Don't go cutting corners. D.

50
00:05:00.425 --> 00:05:04.429
Already cashed my paycheck.
You'll get it updated right. Hear me?

51
00:05:04.512 --> 00:05:07.221
Mom. seriously!
Just feed the washer. alright?

52
00:05:07.305 --> 00:05:09.682
I forgot this time. I told you.

53
00:05:10.598 --> 00:05:12.433
Promise me you'll buy the update.

54
00:05:12.516 --> 00:05:14.257
Okay. okay.

55
00:05:14.817 --> 00:05:17.282
And you're really going to school
dressed like that?

56
00:05:17.395 --> 00:05:18.608
Uniform’s soaked.

57
00:05:18.672 --> 00:05:21.462
A military-grade implant was
found missing from the body

58
00:05:21.465 --> 00:05:24.385
of Lt. Col. James Norris.
shot dead by MaxTac…

59
00:05:24.492 --> 00:05:27.584
Mom. you're on TV! Nova!

60
00:05:27.691 --> 00:05:30.017
Not Nova. David. A bloodbath.

61
00:05:30.821 --> 00:05:33.707
- Go on. Off to school.
- Bye.

62
00:05:34.125 --> 00:05:35.668
Love you. Miho.

63
00:05:40.757 --> 00:05:43.162
Maine? It's Gloria.

64
00:05:50.607 --> 00:05:51.607
Hm…

65
00:06:30.970 --> 00:06:34.123
Trauma Team.
Clear a path immediately.

66
00:06:34.833 --> 00:06:38.086
Emergency evac underway.
Emergency evac.

67
00:06:38.178 --> 00:06:40.447
All AVs. vacate the airway.

68
00:06:40.976 --> 00:06:45.314
Trauma Team. Clear a path immediately.
Trauma Team. Clear a path.

69
00:06:45.324 --> 00:06:46.416
Don't walk.

70
00:06:48.147 --> 00:06:49.231
Don't walk.

71
00:06:50.926 --> 00:06:54.645
Walk. Walk. Walk.

72
00:06:55.190 --> 00:06:57.609
Walk. Walk.

73
00:08:01.163 --> 00:08:02.828
Good morning to you. class.

74
00:08:02.831 --> 00:08:05.623
Today's attendance:
Zero absences.

75
00:08:06.055 --> 00:08:07.495
Martinez. David:

76
00:08:07.498 --> 00:08:10.138
You are not in compliance
with the Academy's dress code.

77
00:08:10.198 --> 00:08:12.117
Yeah. Real sorry about that.

78
00:08:12.120 --> 00:08:14.240
Afraid my uniform's still
at the cleaner's.

79
00:08:14.410 --> 00:08:16.370
Do you have a spare uniform?

80
00:08:16.407 --> 00:08:17.867
Yeah. Spare's there too.

81
00:08:17.896 --> 00:08:21.962
Understood. Please submit a
Uniform Exception form after class.

82
00:08:22.164 --> 00:08:24.350
Now. let us begin today's lesson.

83
00:08:24.420 --> 00:08:27.744
- You will observe…
- Gutter rat. Rat off the street.

84
00:08:27.965 --> 00:08:30.376
Me? Nah. Wouldn't show my face.

85
00:08:30.455 --> 00:08:33.609
Cray. I know.
but some of us here to learn to learn.

86
00:08:34.155 --> 00:08:35.948
With that fossiltech?

87
00:08:36.098 --> 00:08:38.601
Updates. man.
Bet it's not compatible.

88
00:08:38.799 --> 00:08:40.379
Made it compatible.

89
00:08:40.686 --> 00:08:42.186
Huh? How?

90
00:08:42.525 --> 00:08:43.859
How I had to.

91
00:08:44.070 --> 00:08:45.819
Life's gotta be-gotta be shit

92
00:08:45.900 --> 00:08:48.361
when a two-bit wreath
costs your life savings.

93
00:08:48.443 --> 00:08:52.782
At this time. I ask all students to log
into the Green Room for meditation.

94
00:08:52.811 --> 00:08:54.313
Countin’ on ya. Doc.

95
00:08:59.205 --> 00:09:00.623
- Seriously?
- What?

96
00:09:00.679 --> 00:09:02.389
Martinez again!

97
00:09:02.706 --> 00:09:04.473
- Come on!
- Not again!

98
00:09:08.881 --> 00:09:11.968
I’m so sorry for the
inconvenience my son has caused.

99
00:09:11.971 --> 00:09:15.144
I wouldn't call this a matter of money.
Mrs. Martinez.

100
00:09:15.382 --> 00:09:19.428
Although I must say it was quite an
expense for us to restore the system.

101
00:09:19.518 --> 00:09:22.334
Of course.
and I will pay for the repairs.

102
00:09:22.337 --> 00:09:23.253
Hm?

103
00:09:23.256 --> 00:09:26.884
As I understand it.
Mr. Martinez modified his headset

104
00:09:26.909 --> 00:09:30.444
with back-alley software
to avoid paying for the licensed update.

105
00:09:30.954 --> 00:09:34.708
This is not behavior befitting a pupil
from a financially stable home.

106
00:09:34.764 --> 00:09:37.668
It's not a problem. really.
We can afford it.

107
00:09:37.907 --> 00:09:39.181
Be that as it may.

108
00:09:39.184 --> 00:09:41.937
I see an opportunity here
to improve David's situation.

109
00:09:42.027 --> 00:09:43.246
Meaning what. exactly?

110
00:09:43.249 --> 00:09:46.566
David is not a good fit
with his classmates.

111
00:09:47.128 --> 00:09:49.547
He could benefit
from a change in environment.

112
00:09:49.550 --> 00:09:52.509
No! Wait. please.
I mean. he has to stay here.

113
00:09:52.715 --> 00:09:56.177
D deserves this education as much
as every other child in this school.

114
00:09:56.313 --> 00:09:58.925
What happened?
Didn't I tell you to get the upgrade?

115
00:09:59.223 --> 00:10:02.118
Yeah. Doc's damn fault.
Gave me a faulty port drive.

116
00:10:02.428 --> 00:10:04.771
You tried to get around the system.
didn't you?

117
00:10:04.954 --> 00:10:06.904
Now. it'll cost us ten times more.

118
00:10:07.360 --> 00:10:08.604
Sorry.

119
00:10:08.811 --> 00:10:10.481
If it's something
you gotta apologize for.

120
00:10:10.484 --> 00:10:12.417
maybe don't do it in the first place. ey?

121
00:10:12.516 --> 00:10:14.935
You said you didn't have
the eddies when I asked. so…

122
00:10:14.938 --> 00:10:16.788
I was waiting for payday!

123
00:10:16.820 --> 00:10:19.907
You know we don't got that
kind of cash just lying around.

124
00:10:19.910 --> 00:10:21.570
Can't you sit still a minute?

125
00:10:25.273 --> 00:10:27.486
You know.
I've been thinkin’ lately.

126
00:10:28.002 --> 00:10:29.319
About what?

127
00:10:29.497 --> 00:10:33.042
Maybe I drop out.
Find some work or whatever.

128
00:10:33.186 --> 00:10:34.771
Do you hear yourself?

129
00:10:34.887 --> 00:10:37.848
C'mon. seriously.
You know we can't afford those repairs.

130
00:10:39.013 --> 00:10:43.644
Plus. you got no idea just how bad
I stand out compared to all of them.

131
00:10:43.682 --> 00:10:46.644
Anyone sides a true blue corpo
gets shit on.

132
00:10:47.339 --> 00:10:49.479
Even if I do graduate.
they'll never accept me.

133
00:10:49.482 --> 00:10:51.705
No kid from Santo will ever be a suit.

134
00:10:51.982 --> 00:10:53.901
Don't wanna be one anyway.

135
00:10:57.644 --> 00:10:58.905
So. you tell me.

136
00:10:58.908 --> 00:11:01.191
What have I been busting
my ass for then. huh?

137
00:11:01.998 --> 00:11:04.887
Everything I do. I do for you. D.

138
00:11:05.254 --> 00:11:06.774
Don't you see that?

139
00:11:08.154 --> 00:11:10.680
You're breaking my heart. Miho.

140
00:11:11.077 --> 00:11:12.114
Wait. What?

141
00:11:12.187 --> 00:11:16.775
My sweet baby boy.
So smart. so talented.

142
00:11:16.885 --> 00:11:18.206
You're everything to me.

143
00:11:18.253 --> 00:11:21.774
I want to give you a fighting chance
in this city and a good education.

144
00:11:22.101 --> 00:11:26.839
It's why I put in all of those hours.
Why I'm never home.

145
00:11:29.024 --> 00:11:30.393
I-I'm sorry.

146
00:11:31.139 --> 00:11:34.793
Shouldn't have brought it up.
Don't cry. Mom.

147
00:11:35.105 --> 00:11:37.277
Think I don't know how they treat you?

148
00:11:37.736 --> 00:11:39.655
Think I don't get treated the same way?

149
00:11:40.968 --> 00:11:43.295
But that's why you gotta prove them wrong.

150
00:11:43.642 --> 00:11:45.894
You have to work hard
and rise through the ranks.

151
00:11:46.038 --> 00:11:49.707
My son at Arasaka Tower top floor!
I can just see it.

152
00:11:50.080 --> 00:11:52.281
You've got this. D.
You're my son.

153
00:11:53.212 --> 00:11:54.922
Yeah. well. easier said than done.

154
00:11:55.365 --> 00:11:56.365
Huh?

155
00:12:01.629 --> 00:12:02.888
Fuck 'em up!

156
00:12:05.386 --> 00:12:08.766
- Don't let 'em get away!
- Suit's limo's titanium plated!

157
00:12:08.769 --> 00:12:11.293
The hunt's on. my beast-bros!

158
00:12:16.739 --> 00:12:17.926
Yeah!

159
00:12:22.960 --> 00:12:24.608
No one fucks with the Animals!

160
00:12:24.618 --> 00:12:25.774
Ara-suckers…

161
00:12:25.776 --> 00:12:27.588
Mom! Brake! Brake hard!

162
00:12:27.591 --> 00:12:29.093
Watch out!

163
00:12:40.487 --> 00:12:42.636
Mom? Mom!

164
00:12:50.436 --> 00:12:53.439
Is that the Trauma Team?
Oh. thank Christ.

165
00:12:56.250 --> 00:12:57.562
He's not a client.

166
00:12:57.623 --> 00:12:58.862
Neither is she.

167
00:12:59.160 --> 00:13:00.302
Hey. wait!

168
00:13:00.362 --> 00:13:03.949
Secure the policyholder.
Leave them to the city meat wagons.

169
00:13:03.952 --> 00:13:05.662
- Copy that.
- What?

170
00:13:05.826 --> 00:13:08.655
What the hell? Hey!
Where are you going?

171
00:13:09.388 --> 00:13:10.388
Shit!

172
00:13:10.831 --> 00:13:12.750
No way.
Just gonna leave us here?

173
00:13:13.097 --> 00:13:15.591
Mom! Momma!

174
00:13:16.111 --> 00:13:17.592
Mom. wake up!

175
00:13:17.791 --> 00:13:19.139
Fucking piece of…

176
00:13:21.025 --> 00:13:23.925
Mom! Dammit. get off me!

177
00:13:24.246 --> 00:13:27.875
Shit. Get the fuck off!
Why won't it... Dammit!

178
00:13:28.987 --> 00:13:29.987
Mom!

179
00:13:31.143 --> 00:13:32.232
Fuck!

180
00:13:36.415 --> 00:13:37.988
Surgery was a success.

181
00:13:38.105 --> 00:13:40.548
Your mother hasn't come to just yet.
but she's stable.

182
00:13:41.320 --> 00:13:43.260
Need her to stay a few more nights.

183
00:13:43.492 --> 00:13:45.825
Oh. Then. is it okay if I see her?

184
00:13:45.908 --> 00:13:49.274
No can do. buddy.
Visitation ain't part of your package.

185
00:13:49.534 --> 00:13:51.013
Oh. Right.

186
00:13:51.089 --> 00:13:53.967
Anyway. I should get started
on the paperwork.

187
00:13:54.071 --> 00:13:55.549
Brought your mom's things.

188
00:13:55.626 --> 00:13:58.504
And don't forget to zip us those EDs.
Got three days.

189
00:13:59.282 --> 00:14:02.727
Yeah. There's a reason everyone
in Night City wants insurance.

190
00:14:03.059 --> 00:14:04.128
Stay safe now.

191
00:14:05.010 --> 00:14:07.513
Yeah. hoop ship. Version back.

192
00:14:08.271 --> 00:14:10.774
Is that all?
You low-balling me? Huh?

193
00:14:11.473 --> 00:14:13.566
Nah. forget it. choom.

194
00:14:14.411 --> 00:14:16.330
Dammit! Hm?

195
00:14:18.983 --> 00:14:20.309
What the fuck?

196
00:14:28.065 --> 00:14:29.891
Another account. Christ.

197
00:14:29.972 --> 00:14:33.434
Just enough. She saved so much.
Never knew.

198
00:14:34.169 --> 00:14:36.336
So. that. it settled the medical.

199
00:14:38.873 --> 00:14:41.514
Still gotta cover rent. Huh?

200
00:14:42.254 --> 00:14:45.607
Doc? Hey. you get the still I sent?
Listen.

201
00:14:45.767 --> 00:14:49.504
Don't think I'd forgotten I owe you a kick
in the nuts for that shoddy bootleg.

202
00:14:50.065 --> 00:14:51.378
But check this.

203
00:14:52.112 --> 00:14:53.291
Cyberware.

204
00:14:53.951 --> 00:14:57.421
Yeah. looks... military. doesn't it?

205
00:14:57.904 --> 00:14:59.580
How do you think it would fetch.

206
00:14:59.648 --> 00:15:02.526
if I was interested
and the price was right?

207
00:15:03.225 --> 00:15:05.060
Not selling.
Just want an estimate.

208
00:15:08.068 --> 00:15:10.728
Nah. fuck that noise.
No way it's that cheap.

209
00:15:13.912 --> 00:15:15.720
Oh. come on. choom.

210
00:15:18.042 --> 00:15:20.085
Whatev! Wasn't selling anyways.

211
00:15:20.202 --> 00:15:23.810
By the way. Don't expect me
to push your XBDs at school anymore!

212
00:15:25.855 --> 00:15:28.542
Any pinchin' hack had
taken me for a gonk.

213
00:15:29.553 --> 00:15:31.493
A Sandevistan.

214
00:15:31.722 --> 00:15:36.143
No serial number and what?
Military-grade. this thing. really?

215
00:15:36.206 --> 00:15:38.692
It definitely ain't legal. But whatev.

216
00:15:40.090 --> 00:15:41.743
The hell are these specs?

217
00:15:54.880 --> 00:15:55.880
Huh?

218
00:16:01.964 --> 00:16:04.144
Little piece of advice. Martinez.

219
00:16:04.514 --> 00:16:07.417
- Learn to take a hint.
- About what?

220
00:16:07.421 --> 00:16:10.338
Our class.
You're not welcome. Got it?

221
00:16:10.427 --> 00:16:12.005
Huh? If this is about yesterday...

222
00:16:12.008 --> 00:16:14.448
- Who said anything about yesterday?
- What?

223
00:16:14.451 --> 00:16:17.935
You probably figure I give you a hard time
'cause you're poor. Simply untrue.

224
00:16:17.964 --> 00:16:19.966
I'm rather charitably inclined.

225
00:16:20.024 --> 00:16:22.757
Not your fault you were born
on the wrong side of society.

226
00:16:23.459 --> 00:16:25.440
There's no rule
that says a street kid

227
00:16:25.443 --> 00:16:28.617
can't make it at the Academy.
provided they pay their way.

228
00:16:28.817 --> 00:16:31.570
What cracks my chrome
is something else entirely.

229
00:16:31.573 --> 00:16:32.989
- Know what?
- Look. choom.

230
00:16:32.992 --> 00:16:35.408
I haven't understood a single
thing coming out of your mouth.

231
00:16:35.411 --> 00:16:36.885
- That right there!
- Hm…

232
00:16:36.888 --> 00:16:39.557
Time to get gone.
Just drop out. why don't ya?

233
00:16:39.661 --> 00:16:41.741
- Huh?
- You're a misfit. an anomaly.

234
00:16:41.744 --> 00:16:44.996
Human but trash. and there's nothing
that can change that.

235
00:16:44.999 --> 00:16:48.189
Rot in you runs as deep
as your bones. Martinez.

236
00:16:48.842 --> 00:16:51.885
Best you can do is not
spread it to the rest of us.

237
00:16:52.049 --> 00:16:53.592
Did I just short-circ?

238
00:16:53.595 --> 00:16:56.473
Said you didn't care
as long as I paid tuition.

239
00:16:56.476 --> 00:16:58.991
I heard your mommy came in
to see the principal.

240
00:16:58.994 --> 00:17:01.185
ask forgiveness for your little stunt.

241
00:17:01.599 --> 00:17:03.885
Caused quite a scene.
crying for her baby boy.

242
00:17:03.887 --> 00:17:05.620
begging for him
not to get expelled.

243
00:17:05.664 --> 00:17:06.981
So shameless.

244
00:17:07.079 --> 00:17:09.695
You know. since we're chatting.
I've just always wondered.

245
00:17:09.704 --> 00:17:13.083
How could she afford to send you
to Arasaka Academy anyway?

246
00:17:13.319 --> 00:17:16.230
Care to explain. Martinez?

247
00:17:16.677 --> 00:17:20.023
Go on. Tell us.
How does Mommy pay your way?

248
00:17:20.816 --> 00:17:24.700
What's any Night City bottom feeder
do to make a quick eurobuck. huh?

249
00:17:25.781 --> 00:17:28.547
A couple of pretty salacious
things come to mind.

250
00:17:28.550 --> 00:17:29.707
Tired of this shit.

251
00:17:29.710 --> 00:17:31.770
Hold on. choom.
Who said we were done?

252
00:17:31.884 --> 00:17:32.884
Fuck off!

253
00:17:44.118 --> 00:17:46.111
What? Huh?

254
00:17:53.218 --> 00:17:56.473
Got anything slotted?
MMA freeware maybe?

255
00:18:22.182 --> 00:18:23.182
Knew it.

256
00:18:23.185 --> 00:18:28.065
Nothing like the Strongarm 400 to bring
out the best in your kung-fu chipware.

257
00:18:28.128 --> 00:18:30.422
Organic knuckles? Seriously?

258
00:18:30.519 --> 00:18:34.064
Wanna try me again?
I suggest you pack some serious chrome.

259
00:18:34.340 --> 00:18:35.989
Or just drop out.

260
00:18:36.073 --> 00:18:37.822
You know what I'd prefer.

261
00:18:44.843 --> 00:18:46.430
Mr. Martinez?

262
00:18:47.325 --> 00:18:50.859
I'm calling in regards
to Gloria Martinez's condition.

263
00:18:51.766 --> 00:18:54.144
- Huh?
- She was stable this morning.

264
00:18:54.273 --> 00:18:57.651
but then her vitals began to
nosedive really out of nowhere.

265
00:18:57.849 --> 00:19:02.525
But you said the surgery was successful.

266
00:19:02.662 --> 00:19:05.998
True. But only so much we
can do on the discount package.

267
00:19:06.049 --> 00:19:09.135
Worn down as she was.
I doubt she'd had lasted much longer.

268
00:19:09.186 --> 00:19:10.702
Overworked. seemed to me.

269
00:19:11.242 --> 00:19:14.482
Anyway. I'm supposed to tell you
we offer some burial options.

270
00:19:14.563 --> 00:19:17.745
People in Night City
want corpo gigs for a reason. kid.

271
00:19:18.604 --> 00:19:21.783
Greetings. valued customer.
We are sorry for your loss.

272
00:19:21.885 --> 00:19:23.916
To ease things at this difficult time.

273
00:19:23.942 --> 00:19:26.027
we can deliver the body
of your dearly departed

274
00:19:26.111 --> 00:19:28.089
to your home or to a funeral home.

275
00:19:28.249 --> 00:19:29.662
Would you like to learn more?

276
00:19:29.665 --> 00:19:31.102
I got a choice?

277
00:19:31.211 --> 00:19:33.797
Is our budget-friendly
cremation service right for you?

278
00:19:33.814 --> 00:19:36.698
Waive those pesky delivery fees
and bring your loved one home today.

279
00:19:36.701 --> 00:19:37.852
Optional...

280
00:19:45.825 --> 00:19:46.952
Don't walk.

281
00:19:47.229 --> 00:19:48.897
Good day. Mrs. Martinez.

282
00:19:48.954 --> 00:19:52.149
We've received a quote for the repairs
to our system infrastructure.

283
00:19:52.152 --> 00:19:55.572
As agreed. I've sent you an e-mail
with the payment details.

284
00:19:55.716 --> 00:19:57.568
Also. perhaps you've had time to think?

285
00:19:57.571 --> 00:19:58.780
Do let me know.

286
00:19:58.864 --> 00:20:00.922
Just say the word and we'll
begin making arrangements

287
00:20:00.925 --> 00:20:02.650
for David's transfer
to another institution.

288
00:20:02.653 --> 00:20:05.617
Please note.
To maintain your utilities contract.

289
00:20:05.620 --> 00:20:08.741
you must pay a penalty
of 500 euro-dollars

290
00:20:08.815 --> 00:20:12.375
in addition to any past
due amounts and late fees.

291
00:20:12.421 --> 00:20:14.339
If you cannot pay by the deadline.

292
00:20:14.376 --> 00:20:17.411
your services will be terminated
in the following order…

293
00:20:18.023 --> 00:20:20.692
Trauma Team.
Clear a path immediately.

294
00:20:21.381 --> 00:20:22.846
Ding-ding. Martinez!

295
00:20:22.889 --> 00:20:24.715
Me again. Time's up.

296
00:20:24.868 --> 00:20:26.676
Rent's long past due.

297
00:20:26.928 --> 00:20:29.762
Keep this shit up and I
won't just change your lock.

298
00:20:29.772 --> 00:20:32.942
I'll throw your ass out on the street.
Ya feel me?

299
00:20:49.404 --> 00:20:52.806
The implant I showed you.
you said you'd take it off me for 10K?

300
00:20:53.737 --> 00:20:56.335
Six now?
Said ten yesterday. choom!

301
00:20:56.436 --> 00:20:58.442
Come on.
That's just one fucking day.

302
00:20:58.445 --> 00:21:00.614
And we both know
that it's worth way more!

303
00:21:00.650 --> 00:21:02.645
Hell yeah. I looked into it. and I...

304
00:21:05.472 --> 00:21:08.478
Oh. yeah?
Well. fuck you too! Bitch.

305
00:21:14.356 --> 00:21:16.956
Katsuo here. I heard about your mom.

306
00:21:17.328 --> 00:21:20.999
I'd offer my sympathies.
but find it hard to sympathize.

307
00:21:21.162 --> 00:21:22.916
God only knows what
she had to endure

308
00:21:22.919 --> 00:21:26.389
to send her delinquent son to
an Academy he doesn't belong at.

309
00:21:27.035 --> 00:21:29.454
Her methods couldn't have been noble

310
00:21:29.538 --> 00:21:33.583
if she died in a car accident.
So mundane.

311
00:21:33.667 --> 00:21:34.710
But you know?

312
00:21:34.793 --> 00:21:37.796
Karma.
There's a lesson in this. David.

313
00:21:39.024 --> 00:21:42.251
Your mother tried to live
beyond her means and died.

314
00:21:42.604 --> 00:21:44.277
Don't make the same mistake.

315
00:22:00.783 --> 00:22:02.663
Christ. The hell. who is that?

316
00:22:03.863 --> 00:22:05.510
David. hey.

317
00:22:06.885 --> 00:22:08.678
That the big bad Sandy?

318
00:22:08.775 --> 00:22:12.278
Not a badge or fixer in town
who's not looking for that beaut.

319
00:22:12.376 --> 00:22:13.601
I told you though…

320
00:22:14.168 --> 00:22:18.005
ain't gonna find anyone sane
willing to take it off your hands.

321
00:22:18.130 --> 00:22:19.423
I'm not here to sell.

322
00:22:20.756 --> 00:22:24.849
I want this fused here.
'Bout time I chrome the fuck up.

322
00:22:25.305 --> 00:23:25.463
